\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Eddie scanned the room, searching for a flicker of doubt, a hint of hesitation. But instead, he saw only a sea of resolute faces, each one etched with a unique story of loss, yet all bound together by a common purpose.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Taking a deep breath to steady his own nerves, Eddie addressed the room once more. "We know this is a big ask," he acknowledged, his voice resonating with sincerity. "We know this is a dangerous path we're about to embark on. But we can't do this alone. Every single one of you has a reason to fight. They've taken your loved ones, your friends, your family. But they haven't taken your spirit. They haven't taken your fight!"}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Silence once again descended upon the room. The students exchanged glances, their faces a mixture of fear and resolve. Then, a small, determined voice broke the tension.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "I'm in," a young woman declared, her voice trembling slightly but her eyes blazing with defiance. "I won't let them get away with this."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 A wave of relief washed over Eddie. One voice had become two, then three, then a chorus. Christine, her face stoic but a flicker of vulnerability in her eyes, finally spoke. "Fine," she conceded, a grudging acceptance in her voice. "But let's get one thing clear \endash  this alliance ends when we get Dominic back."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Geralt echoed her sentiment with a curt nod. "We're here for Dominic. Nothing more."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Will, his eyes gleaming with newfound hope, added, "And for Madeleine. And for everyone else they've taken."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Ashley looking Eddie with a smile latent with pride said, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93We can do this. We have to.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 One by one, others echoed her sentiment. A ripple of agreement spread through the room, gathering momentum with each voice that joined the chorus. The fear hadn't vanished, but it was overshadowed by a fierce determination, a collective will to fight for justice.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "We won't promise it will be easy," Eddie continued, his voice ringing with conviction. "There will be challenges, dangers\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8230\'85 But we will face them together. Because giving up is not an option. Not when our loved ones are counting on us to bring them home!"}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 A collective cheer erupted from the crowd, a raw, primal sound that resonated with the pain and anger festering within them. This wasn't just a gathering anymore; it was the birth of a resistance, fueled by love and loss. Eddie glanced at Will and his bandmates, their faces alight with determination. He spotted Ashley next to him, a small smile playing on her lips as she watched the scene unfold. They had a long road ahead, but for the first time since Madeleine's disappearance, a flicker of hope danced in his heart. They weren't alone. They had an army. And together, they would find Madeleine and dismantle the Black Hand, one way or another. }}